---
description: Keep all source in English (identifiers, comments, UI copy, file names)
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx,js,css,html}"
alwaysApply: true
---

# English-only codebase

Use **English** for:

- File and folder names (except established vendor paths).
- Identifiers: variables, functions, types, interfaces, enums, and class members.
- User-visible strings in the UI and API error messages surfaced to users.
- Code comments and documentation inside the repo.

Do not introduce Spanish (or other non-English) naming or copy in application source unless it is a required literal from an external contract or legal text.
